1
00:00:04,379 --> 00:00:05,339
[Growls]

2
00:00:05,380 --> 00:00:06,507
[Dolphins chatter]

3
00:00:10,135 --> 00:00:11,261
[Screeches]

4
00:00:13,055 --> 00:00:14,139
J Adventure time J

5
00:00:14,181 --> 00:00:15,432
J Come on, grab your friends &

6
00:00:15,516 --> 00:00:18,227
> We'll go
to very distant lands 7

7
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:20,521
J With Finn and Jake
and Susan Strong J

8
00:00:20,646 --> 00:00:22,272
J And possibly BMO 7

9
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:24,107
J It's adventure time 7

10
00:00:33,408 --> 00:00:37,329
CANDY CHILD: "Mom! I wanna
play outside with Consuelo!"

11
00:00:37,412 --> 00:00:40,541
"Cool your jets!
It's super dangerous outside.

12
00:00:40,582 --> 00:00:42,709
Little kids have to stay
in the castle."

13
00:00:42,793 --> 00:00:44,461
"But I'm rowdy!"

14
00:00:44,586 --> 00:00:49,174
"Yeah, well, but look.
See what happens?

15
00:00:49,216 --> 00:00:51,051
You want a playdate with death?

16
00:00:51,093 --> 00:00:53,220
That's why you have to
stay inside!

17
00:00:53,303 --> 00:00:55,973
And 'cause Consuelo's mom
is a pain in the neck."

18
00:00:55,973 --> 00:00:57,432
[Gasps]

19
00:00:58,183 --> 00:01:02,312
In the heat of the sun, you burn
like a pink little baby!

20
00:01:02,354 --> 00:01:03,188
CANDY CHILD; Aah!

21
00:01:03,230 --> 00:01:05,941
- What?
- Oh! A scweam!

22
00:01:05,941 --> 00:01:07,150
Aah!

23
00:01:07,192 --> 00:01:09,570
Well, now, what seems
to be the trouble?

24
00:01:09,653 --> 00:01:11,446
I saw something in the water!

25
00:01:11,530 --> 00:01:13,532
And I was like, "No, thanks!"

26
00:01:13,574 --> 00:01:15,325
Out of my way, muffin man!

27
00:01:15,409 --> 00:01:16,952
How rude.

28
00:01:17,077 --> 00:01:21,206
Well, whatever that little girl
saw will be a mystery forever.

29
00:01:25,168 --> 00:01:29,548
SHIP: Transport for Seeker
XJ-7-7 "Strong" has arrived.

30
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:32,593
Please verify identity
as "Strong."

31
00:01:32,676 --> 00:01:36,722
Oh! Trust me, I'm strong indeed!

32
00:01:36,805 --> 00:01:38,473
Pow, pow!
[Chuckles]

33
00:01:38,473 --> 00:01:40,309
Ah? Not enough?

34
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:42,603
You need to feel them guns?

35
00:01:42,686 --> 00:01:44,062
Verifying.

36
00:01:44,104 --> 00:01:47,232
Whoa!
Well, hello, frisky!

37
00:01:47,316 --> 00:01:48,233
[Giggles]

38
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:51,612
Todd, I'm right here!

39
00:01:51,612 --> 00:01:54,448
Identifying dangerous mutant.

40
00:01:54,489 --> 00:01:56,450
Initiating defensive mode.

41
00:01:56,491 --> 00:01:58,368
[Splashing]

42
00:02:01,330 --> 00:02:02,581
Seeking human.

43
00:02:02,623 --> 00:02:05,751
-[Screaming ]
- Human, come home to safety.

44
00:02:05,834 --> 00:02:06,752
Seeking human.

45
00:02:06,877 --> 00:02:09,546
Human, come home to safety.

46
00:02:12,174 --> 00:02:14,176
FINN:
Hey, Jake, what about this one?

47
00:02:14,926 --> 00:02:17,262
[Laughs ]Great.

48
00:02:17,304 --> 00:02:19,640
We're gonna look so great
for this funeral.

49
00:02:19,681 --> 00:02:21,433
BMO:
How do you like my bandeau!

50
00:02:21,558 --> 00:02:24,936
I was too embarrassed
to get a bra fitting.

51
00:02:24,936 --> 00:02:28,565
I know they are professionals,
but it's just too intimate.

52
00:02:28,649 --> 00:02:29,691
You look great!

53
00:02:29,775 --> 00:02:31,401
Settlement detected.

54
00:02:31,443 --> 00:02:34,446
Continuing search for XJ-7-7.

55
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:36,948
BANANA GUARD:
Get him! Attack! Attack!

56
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:38,158
TOGETHER: Aaah!

57
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:41,036
Hostile cylinders detected.

58
00:02:41,078 --> 00:02:42,954
Release countermeasures.

59
00:02:43,038 --> 00:02:44,164
TOGETHER: Aah!

60
00:02:44,206 --> 00:02:45,082
[Muffled]Ahh!

61
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:47,584
Hostile cylinders immobilized.

62
00:02:49,670 --> 00:02:51,797
Engaging hostile bobbleheads.

63
00:02:54,591 --> 00:02:56,301
Neutralizing.

64
00:02:56,343 --> 00:02:59,971
Please do not turn your system
off during neutralization.

65
00:03:01,431 --> 00:03:02,599
[Crash! ]

66
00:03:02,724 --> 00:03:04,476
FINN:
Holy mud!

67
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:07,062
It took out the gumball guards
like they was nothin'!

68
00:03:07,104 --> 00:03:08,605
BMO doesn't like it!

69
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:11,692
We gotta chop this thing
into smashaghetti.

70
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:13,860
Yaaaaaaaaaa!

71
00:03:13,944 --> 00:03:16,071
I'll take you out
with these hug nubs!

72
00:03:16,113 --> 00:03:18,490
Yaaaaal!
I'll help you, Finn!

73
00:03:18,573 --> 00:03:21,118
Aah! Help me, Finn!

74
00:03:21,118 --> 00:03:21,952
Oof!

75
00:03:21,993 --> 00:03:23,995
Hostile mutant neutralized.

76
00:03:24,079 --> 00:03:24,955
[Gulps]

77
00:03:24,996 --> 00:03:26,707
[Thinking ]
You got this, Finn Mertens.

78
00:03:26,748 --> 00:03:28,500
You're a buff
little bionic baby.

79
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:31,336
Rush!
Ruuuuussshhh!

80
00:03:31,378 --> 00:03:32,629
Rush!

81
00:03:32,754 --> 00:03:33,630
[Grunts]

82
00:03:33,714 --> 00:03:35,465
Aaahhh!

83
00:03:35,507 --> 00:03:38,135
SHIP: Verifying.
Human identified.

84
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:43,265
Infant PG-8-7 "Mertens."

85
00:03:43,265 --> 00:03:46,017
-[Whoosh! ]
- Aaah -- Oh.

86
00:03:46,143 --> 00:03:48,145
[Whirring]

87
00:03:48,145 --> 00:03:49,771
PG-8-7.

88
00:03:49,896 --> 00:03:51,898
Uh...you mean me?

89
00:03:52,482 --> 00:03:56,903
You will assist this transport
in locating Seeker XJ-7-7.

90
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:02,784
PG-8-7 "Mertens,"
please climb aboard.

91
00:04:02,784 --> 00:04:05,162
Please climb aboard.
Come on.

92
00:04:05,287 --> 00:04:09,249
"Mertens?"
Wait, do you, like, know me?

93
00:04:14,129 --> 00:04:16,965
Got it! Great work
distractin' 'em, Finn!

94
00:04:17,007 --> 00:04:19,009
You okay, dude?

95
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:22,012
I feel like that ship
might've been important.

96
00:04:22,137 --> 00:04:23,513
But I'm fine.

97
00:04:23,513 --> 00:04:25,891
Yeah, my hands are a little sore
from smashing,

98
00:04:26,016 --> 00:04:27,642
but I'm fine, too.

99
00:04:27,642 --> 00:04:29,644
Eeeeeeeyaaaa!

100
00:04:29,644 --> 00:04:33,023
Ha! Ha! Once again
BMO comes out on top!

101
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:35,150
- Bzzt!
- BMO!

102
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:36,651
BMO, you okay?

103
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,029
Signal received.

104
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:41,907
XJ-7-7 requests transport.

105
00:04:42,741 --> 00:04:44,910
BOTH:
[Gasps ]Susan!

106
00:04:49,164 --> 00:04:50,290
Hey.

107
00:04:50,373 --> 00:04:51,875
Hi, Finn.

108
00:04:51,917 --> 00:04:54,669
Uh, sorry again
my grass arm busted you up.

109
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:55,879
It's okay.

110
00:04:55,921 --> 00:04:59,007
At the time,
Susan was gonna bust you up.

111
00:04:59,049 --> 00:05:01,802
Where's Jake?
Is he okay?

112
00:05:01,885 --> 00:05:03,887
He's outside.
He's bringing the ship over.

113
00:05:03,929 --> 00:05:05,055
The ship?

114
00:05:08,683 --> 00:05:11,061
On. Ship.

115
00:05:11,061 --> 00:05:12,687
BMO:
[Humming]

116
00:05:14,564 --> 00:05:17,692
How about it, Suze?
Does any of this look familiar?

117
00:05:17,818 --> 00:05:20,654
Me and Finn took this whole
bad block down ourselves!

118
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:24,282
Took a bit of finagling, but I
never hunt what I can't catch.

119
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:35,836
[Whoosh! ]

120
00:05:36,837 --> 00:05:38,839
[Drumbeats]

121
00:05:38,922 --> 00:05:41,049
[Whirring]

122
00:05:41,716 --> 00:05:43,051
[Crashing]

123
00:05:50,725 --> 00:05:52,853
BUBBLEGUM:
Hey. Looking for this?

124
00:05:53,436 --> 00:05:55,981
I've been holding on to the
remnants of your cranial implant

125
00:05:55,981 --> 00:05:58,233
since you kidnapped Finn
and almost killed Jake.

126
00:05:58,233 --> 00:05:59,359
You remember that?

127
00:05:59,442 --> 00:06:02,946
I'm running a comparative
mass spec test now.

128
00:06:02,988 --> 00:06:04,239
-[Ding! ]
- Yep.

129
00:06:04,322 --> 00:06:06,491
Looks like both your implant
and the ship

130
00:06:06,491 --> 00:06:08,702
have the same
technological origin.

131
00:06:08,743 --> 00:06:10,495
Human technology.

132
00:06:10,579 --> 00:06:12,205
-[Beep]
- BMO: Finished.

133
00:06:12,247 --> 00:06:13,999
Looks like
BMOQO's finally downloaded

134
00:06:13,999 --> 00:06:15,625
the ship's last commands.

135
00:06:15,709 --> 00:06:17,252
BMO:
Signal received.

136
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:19,337
Proceed to extraction point.

137
00:06:19,379 --> 00:06:25,385
Return Seeker XJ-7-7 and cargo
to Founders Island, home.

138
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:27,387
BMO, can you give us printouts?

139
00:06:28,138 --> 00:06:30,640
Yes, okay.
Printing.

140
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:36,771
Hmm. Man, this island's
way far out there.

141
00:06:39,274 --> 00:06:41,651
Susan needs to go back here.

142
00:06:41,735 --> 00:06:42,903
To this island.

143
00:06:42,986 --> 00:06:47,657
Not sure why.
Susan having crazy week.

144
00:06:47,741 --> 00:06:50,535
I don't know, Susan.
It's so far.

145
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:52,662
Even I don't know
what's out there.

146
00:06:52,787 --> 00:06:55,248
It's a pretty risky
solo mission.

147
00:06:55,290 --> 00:06:56,541
I'm going, too.

148
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:59,502
I mean, we gotta find out
where this ship came from.

149
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:00,670
There could be more of them.

150
00:07:00,754 --> 00:07:02,505
And if this is human-made,

151
00:07:02,547 --> 00:07:04,758
then there might be
other humans on that island.

152
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:07,010
That'd be cool to see, right?

153
00:07:07,052 --> 00:07:08,637
I'll come, too!

154
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:10,055
And so will we.

155
00:07:10,138 --> 00:07:11,681
No, we won't.

156
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:12,682
Oh.

157
00:07:12,766 --> 00:07:15,018
Well, it sounds like
you're all determined.

158
00:07:15,060 --> 00:07:16,686
You should borrow my boat,
though.

159
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:18,021
This thing is trashed.

160
00:07:18,063 --> 00:07:19,689
We don't need a boat!

161
00:07:19,689 --> 00:07:23,068
Have you forgotten?
With a little imagination...

162
00:07:23,193 --> 00:07:27,948
J I can be anything
that you could ever... &

163
00:07:28,031 --> 00:07:29,449
Oh, I lost focus.

164
00:07:29,532 --> 00:07:31,201
Hey,yeah.
Can we borrow your boat?

165
00:07:34,537 --> 00:07:36,081
Are you up here, Fern?

166
00:07:37,165 --> 00:07:40,210
Hey, thanks for letting me crash
on the roof.

167
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:41,419
It's nice up here.

168
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:45,298
Stay as long you want.
I came up here to ask a favor.

169
00:07:45,340 --> 00:07:48,677
I might be gone
for a while on this trip, see,

170
00:07:48,718 --> 00:07:53,098
and I need someone to, uh,
cover for me here in Ooo.

171
00:07:54,224 --> 00:07:55,308
Are you sure?

172
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:59,187
I mean, hero biz
is your whole thing,

173
00:07:59,229 --> 00:08:01,940
and whatever I am, I'm not you.

174
00:08:01,982 --> 00:08:04,442
You can just do your own thing
with it.

175
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:07,821
Like...if some huge
gross monster's

176
00:08:07,862 --> 00:08:09,948
gonna do murder
on a buncha innocents,

177
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:11,324
uh, kill it.

178
00:08:11,366 --> 00:08:14,327
But Kill it you-styles.
Just don't go nuts.

179
00:08:14,369 --> 00:08:17,080
Okay, I can handle that.

180
00:08:17,122 --> 00:08:18,748
Thanks for trusting me.

181
00:08:18,873 --> 00:08:20,750
No, thank you, Fern.

182
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:22,210
I better go pack.

183
00:08:26,381 --> 00:08:27,841
- Eh. Let's figure out...
- We should figure out...

184
00:08:27,882 --> 00:08:29,009
-...something better.
-...a better thing.

185
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:33,930
Hey, Dad?

186
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:36,182
JAKE: Charlie! Hi, it's me!
It's Dad!

187
00:08:36,266 --> 00:08:39,144
I have to go on a sea voyage,
honey! I wanted to say bye!

188
00:08:39,185 --> 00:08:40,937
That's cool.

189
00:08:41,021 --> 00:08:43,148
Hey, you can't see this shirt,
right?

190
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:45,942
This shirt has like four
different breakfasts on it.

191
00:08:45,942 --> 00:08:50,196
JAKE: I can't hear anything!
Bye, love you! Mwah!

192
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:52,782
Mm-kay, Dad!
I'll tell the other pups!

193
00:08:52,824 --> 00:08:54,701
JAKE:
And I'm telling the other pups!

194
00:08:59,956 --> 00:09:02,333
Aww, I'm gonna miss you
so much, Lady.

195
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:05,462
[Speaking Korean]

196
00:09:10,467 --> 00:09:12,427
Finn, did you bring
your nail clippers?

197
00:09:12,469 --> 00:09:14,095
Uh...l think so.

198
00:09:14,095 --> 00:09:15,972
Cool, I forgot to.

199
00:09:15,972 --> 00:09:17,474
Bye, treehouse!

200
00:09:18,808 --> 00:09:21,186
Goodbye, creator!

201
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:24,939
Now me and BMO
can really "out loose!"

202
00:09:24,981 --> 00:09:28,985
Look, BMO! I am pretending
to trash a hotel room!

203
00:09:29,694 --> 00:09:30,570
BMO?

204
00:09:35,867 --> 00:09:37,494
BMO:
[Softly]Ouch.

205
00:09:37,577 --> 00:09:39,746
Thanks for seeing us off, guys.

206
00:09:39,871 --> 00:09:42,749
Yeah, of course.
It's my boat.

207
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:45,085
And we care about him,
you dingus!

208
00:09:45,126 --> 00:09:47,003
Come on!

209
00:09:47,003 --> 00:09:50,131
Sorry,
Marcy is up past her bedtime.

210
00:09:50,131 --> 00:09:51,591
No, it's true.

211
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:54,636
I want you to be
really careful out there.

212
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:56,221
Don't worry.
We've got Susan.

213
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:57,889
That's not what I mean.

214
00:09:57,889 --> 00:10:01,267
Finn, I get the sense that this
trip's more important to you

215
00:10:01,351 --> 00:10:02,519
than you're letting on.

216
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:04,646
I mean,
if you make it to that island,

217
00:10:04,646 --> 00:10:07,273
you might find out
some pretty heavy stuff.

218
00:10:07,357 --> 00:10:09,901
About the humans
and where you came from.

219
00:10:09,984 --> 00:10:11,903
About yourself.

220
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:15,281
Alls I'm saying is,
you have to promise me --

221
00:10:15,365 --> 00:10:18,910
promise me --
that you'll come home safe.

222
00:10:18,993 --> 00:10:20,245


223
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:21,788
- Hi, Bonnie!
- BOTH: Ah!

224
00:10:21,788 --> 00:10:24,415
I'm Fern.
I kind of already know you.

225
00:10:24,541 --> 00:10:26,292
I have a lot
of fuzzy half-memories

226
00:10:26,376 --> 00:10:27,544
from when I was this guy.

227
00:10:27,544 --> 00:10:29,170
Well, just keep the ones
where she's our boss

228
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:30,672
and forget everything else.

229
00:10:30,672 --> 00:10:32,048
SUSAN; Finn?

230
00:10:32,132 --> 00:10:34,926
Hey, good morning.

231
00:10:35,009 --> 00:10:37,387
Boat's loaded, ready to go.

232
00:10:41,558 --> 00:10:43,768
- Ahh! I flinched!
- It's cool.

233
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:46,312
We'll be back soon, I promise!

234
00:10:46,396 --> 00:10:48,773
Bye, kids!
Don't be naughty!

235
00:10:48,815 --> 00:10:51,067
BUBBLEGUM:
Bye! Good luck!

236
00:10:51,151 --> 00:10:52,652
He'll be safe.

237
00:10:52,694 --> 00:10:56,072
Hey, aren't you that dude that
totaled Starchy's motorcycle?

238
00:10:56,156 --> 00:10:58,575
[Waves crashing]

239
00:11:17,969 --> 00:11:19,971
This party is so crazy!

